> This smoky lentil and carrot soup is packed with smoky bacon and infused with herbaceous thyme—our fresh spin on hearty French-style lentil soup. Sprinkle those lucky bowls with umami-rich Parmesan cheese just before serving, and serve with crisp, buttery garlic ciabatta toasts for dipping.

Heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If your bacon is lean, add a drizzle of oil to the pan to help crisp it.

Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Reserve any bacon fat in a #small bowl{} for use in Step 5. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop bacon.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and dice @carrots{6%ounce} into 1/4-inch pieces. Strip half the @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves (all for 4 servings) from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add carrots and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @lentils{1%unit} and their liquid, chopped thyme, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit}, @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce}, and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until carrots are tender and flavors have melded, ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove from heat.

While soup cooks, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{2} in a #toaster{}. Spread with @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}; halve on a diagonal.

Stir @plain butter{1%tbsp} into #pot{} with soup and gently mash about half the lentils with the back of a #wooden spoon{}.

> TIP: If you have any reserved bacon fat, stir in as much as you like for added flavor.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; top with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and bacon. Serve with garlic toasts on the side.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.